The paper deals with the problem of gathering mobile agents in a network, which is a classic problem in distributed computing and falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also involves algorithms and complexity analysis, which are topics in the sub-category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The paper's focus on network topology and communication constraints makes it relevant to the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). The paper's solution to the leader election problem and the gossiping problem also falls under the sub-categories of Algorithms (cs.AL) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), respectively.
